---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { products } from '../../data/products';
import type { Product } from '../../data/products';

const ecoflowSlugs = ['ecoflow-delta-2', 'ecoflow-delta-2-max', 'ecoflow-delta-pro'];
const jackerySlugs = ['jackery-explorer-500', 'jackery-explorer-1000-pro'];

const ecoflowProducts = ecoflowSlugs.map(slug => products.find(p => p.slug === slug)!).filter(Boolean) as Product[];
const jackeryProducts = jackerySlugs.map(slug => products.find(p => p.slug === slug)!).filter(Boolean) as Product[];
const allProducts = [...ecoflowProducts, ...jackeryProducts];
---

<Layout
  title="EcoFlow vs Jackery: Full Comparison (2026)"
  description="EcoFlow vs Jackery — which brand makes better portable power stations? We compared both across every price tier and every spec that matters."
>
  <div class="bg-amber-50 border-b border-amber-100">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-2 text-xs text-amber-800 text-center">
      This site earns commissions from purchases made through our links at no extra cost to you.
    </div>
  </div>

  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">

    <nav class="text-xs text-gray-400 mb-6">
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-green-700">Home</a>
      <span class="mx-2">›</span>
      <a href="/backup-power" class="hover:text-green-700">Backup Power</a>
      <span class="mx-2">›</span>
      EcoFlow vs Jackery
    </nav>

    <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3 leading-tight">
      EcoFlow vs Jackery: Full Comparison (2026)
    </h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-8">Last updated: April 2026 · 5 products across both brands</p>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-8 leading-relaxed">
      EcoFlow and Jackery are the two most recognized names in portable power stations. If you've done
      any research on this category, you've likely already narrowed it down to one of these two brands.
      Here's the honest head-to-head: where each brand wins, where they fall short, and which to choose
      based on how you plan to use it.
    </p>

    <!-- Verdict Box -->
    <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-10">
      <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-2xl p-5">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-700 uppercase tracking-widest mb-2">Choose EcoFlow if...</p>
        <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm text-gray-700">
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-green-600 flex-shrink-0">✓</span>Home backup is your primary use case</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-green-600 flex-shrink-0">✓</span>You want the fastest charging speed</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-green-600 flex-shrink-0">✓</span>You're pairing with solar panels (higher solar input)</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-green-600 flex-shrink-0">✓</span>LFP battery longevity matters to you</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-green-600 flex-shrink-0">✓</span>You want more capacity per dollar</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-100 rounded-2xl p-5">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-blue-700 uppercase tracking-widest mb-2">Choose Jackery if...</p>
        <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm text-gray-700">
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-blue-500 flex-shrink-0">✓</span>Weight and portability are your top priority</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-blue-500 flex-shrink-0">✓</span>You're primarily using it for camping</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-blue-500 flex-shrink-0">✓</span>You prefer simpler controls with less to configure</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-blue-500 flex-shrink-0">✓</span>You value longer established brand track record</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-blue-500 flex-shrink-0">✓</span>You find EcoFlow units frequently sold out</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Brand Criteria Table -->
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Head-to-Head: Brand Comparison</h2>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-12 rounded-xl border border-gray-100">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50 border-b border-gray-200">
            <th class="text-left p-3 font-semibold text-gray-700 w-1/3">Criteria</th>
            <th class="text-left p-3 font-semibold text-green-700">EcoFlow</th>
            <th class="text-left p-3 font-semibold text-blue-700">Jackery</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="text-sm text-gray-700">
          <tr class="border-b border-gray-100">
            <td class="p-3 font-medium text-gray-900">Battery Chemistry</td>
            <td class="p-3">LFP on most models (3,000+ cycles)</td>
            <td class="p-3">NMC on most models (~500 cycles)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-gray-100 bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-3 font-medium text-gray-900">AC Charge Speed</td>
            <td class="p-3">43–50 min to 80% (best in class)</td>
            <td class="p-3">1.8–7 hours to full (varies by model)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-gray-100">
            <td class="p-3 font-medium text-gray-900">Solar Input</td>
            <td class="p-3">500–1,600W depending on model</td>
            <td class="p-3">100–200W (significantly lower)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-gray-100 bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-3 font-medium text-gray-900">Capacity per Dollar</td>
            <td class="p-3">Better — more Wh per $1 spent</td>
            <td class="p-3">Lower — you pay a brand premium</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-gray-100">
            <td class="p-3 font-medium text-gray-900">Weight</td>
            <td class="p-3">Heavier (27–48 lbs for home models)</td>
            <td class="p-3">Lighter (13–25 lbs across lineup)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-gray-100 bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-3 font-medium text-gray-900">App Quality</td>
            <td class="p-3">Feature-rich, more options to configure</td>
            <td class="p-3">Simpler, fewer features, easier to use</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-gray-100">
            <td class="p-3 font-medium text-gray-900">Brand History</td>
            <td class="p-3">Founded 2017, rapid growth</td>
            <td class="p-3">Founded 2012, longer consumer track record</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-gray-100 bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-3 font-medium text-gray-900">Expandability</td>
            <td class="p-3">Yes — Extra Batteries available</td>
            <td class="p-3">Limited — most models standalone</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-gray-100">
            <td class="p-3 font-medium text-gray-900">Warranty</td>
            <td class="p-3">5 years (DELTA Pro), 2 years standard</td>
            <td class="p-3">2 years standard</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-gray-100 bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-3 font-medium text-gray-900">EPS/UPS Mode</td>
            <td class="p-3">Yes — sub-30ms switchover on most models</td>
            <td class="p-3">No automatic switchover feature</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <!-- Tier by Tier -->
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Head-to-Head by Price Tier</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6 mb-12">
      <div class="border border-gray-100 rounded-xl p-5">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">Under $400 — Jackery wins</p>
        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <div>
            <p class="font-medium text-gray-900 mb-1">Jackery Explorer 500 — $349</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">518Wh, 13.3 lbs, simple controls. The go-to for camping and light backup. Often on sale at $249.</p>
            <a href={jackeryProducts[0]?.affiliateUrl} target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" class="text-xs text-green-700 hover:underline">Check on Amazon →</a>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-3 text-sm text-gray-600">
            <p>EcoFlow doesn't have a strong competitor under $400. The Bluetti EB3A ($199) is the best alternative at this price tier, but it's not an EcoFlow.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-green-200 bg-green-50 rounded-xl p-5">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-700 uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">$400–$600 — EcoFlow wins clearly</p>
        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <div>
            <p class="font-medium text-gray-900 mb-1">EcoFlow DELTA 2 — $499</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">1024Wh LFP, 1800W output, 50-min charge to 80%. Twice the capacity of Jackery 500 for $150 more.</p>
            <a href={ecoflowProducts[0]?.affiliateUrl} target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" class="text-xs text-green-700 hover:underline">Check on Amazon →</a>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="font-medium text-gray-900 mb-1">No Jackery equivalent</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">The closest Jackery is the 500 at $349, which has half the capacity. EcoFlow dominates this price range.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-green-200 bg-green-50 rounded-xl p-5">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-700 uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">$700–$1,000 — EcoFlow wins on specs, Jackery competitive on weight</p>
        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <div>
            <p class="font-medium text-gray-900 mb-1">EcoFlow DELTA 2 Max — $999</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">2048Wh LFP, 2400W, expandable to 6144Wh, 1000W solar input. Best in class on every spec.</p>
            <a href={ecoflowProducts[1]?.affiliateUrl} target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" class="text-xs text-green-700 hover:underline">Check on Amazon →</a>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="font-medium text-gray-900 mb-1">Jackery Explorer 1000 Pro — $799</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">1002Wh NMC, 1000W, 1.8-hr charge, 25.4 lbs. Better for camping. Loses on capacity, battery chemistry, and solar input.</p>
            <a href={jackeryProducts[1]?.affiliateUrl} target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" class="text-xs text-green-700 hover:underline">Check on Amazon →</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Individual product cards -->
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8">All Products in This Comparison</h2>

    {allProducts.map((product) => (
      <section id={product.slug} class="mb-12 scroll-mt-20">
        <div class="border border-gray-100 rounded-2xl p-6">
          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-start justify-between gap-4 mb-4">
            <div>
              <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mb-1 {product.brand === 'EcoFlow' ? 'text-green-700' : 'text-blue-600'}">
                {product.brand}
              </p>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">{product.name}</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm">${product.price} &nbsp;·&nbsp; ⭐ {product.rating}/5</p>
            </div>
            <a
              href={product.affiliateUrl}
              target="_blank"
              rel="nofollow noopener"
              class="inline-block bg-green-700 text-white px-5 py-2.5 rounded-lg font-semibold text-sm hover:bg-green-800 transition-colors whitespace-nowrap"
            >
              Check on Amazon →
            </a>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl p-4 mb-4">
            <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-x-8">
              {Object.entries(product.specs).map(([key, val]) => (
                <div class="flex justify-between py-1.5 border-b border-gray-100 last:border-0">
                  <span class="text-gray-500 text-sm">{key}</span>
                  <span class="font-medium text-gray-900 text-sm">{val}</span>
                </div>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2 text-sm">Pros</p>
              <ul class="space-y-1.5">
                {product.pros.map(pro => (
                  <li class="text-sm text-gray-700 flex gap-2">
                    <span class="text-green-600 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">✓</span>{pro}
                  </li>
                ))}
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2 text-sm">Cons</p>
              <ul class="space-y-1.5">
                {product.cons.map(con => (
                  <li class="text-sm text-gray-700 flex gap-2">
                    <span class="text-red-500 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">✗</span>{con}
                  </li>
                ))}
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    ))}

    <section class="border-t border-gray-100 pt-10 mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Is EcoFlow or Jackery more reliable long-term?</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">Jackery has a longer consumer track record (founded 2012 vs EcoFlow's 2017) and fewer reported software-related issues. EcoFlow's hardware quality has improved substantially since 2020 and their LFP batteries will physically outlast Jackery's NMC batteries by 5–6× in cycle count. For home backup where the unit sits plugged in most of the time, EcoFlow's battery chemistry advantage matters more than brand age.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Which brand has better customer support?</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">Jackery has historically had slightly better customer service reviews in the U.S., with faster response times and less friction on warranty claims. EcoFlow has improved significantly and now offers 24-month warranties with a 5-year option on the DELTA Pro line. Both brands handle the U.S. market with domestic support teams. Either is serviceable; neither is exceptional.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Can I use EcoFlow or Jackery as a UPS for my home office?</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">EcoFlow, yes — most DELTA models have an EPS (Emergency Power Supply) mode with sub-30ms switchover, meaning your devices stay on through an outage without interruption. Jackery does not have this feature; there's a detectable gap when switching to battery. If seamless power continuity for computers or servers matters, EcoFlow is the clear choice.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="border-t border-gray-100 pt-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Related Guides</h2>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <a href="/backup-power/best-portable-power-station-under-500" class="group block border border-gray-100 rounded-xl p-4 hover:border-green-200 hover:shadow-sm transition-all">
          <p class="text-xs text-green-700 font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mb-1">Backup Power</p>
          <p class="font-medium text-gray-900 text-sm group-hover:text-green-700 transition-colors">Best Portable Power Stations Under $500 →</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/backup-power/best-portable-power-station-under-1000" class="group block border border-gray-100 rounded-xl p-4 hover:border-green-200 hover:shadow-sm transition-all">
          <p class="text-xs text-green-700 font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mb-1">Backup Power</p>
          <p class="font-medium text-gray-900 text-sm group-hover:text-green-700 transition-colors">Best Portable Power Stations Under $1,000 →</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

  </article>
</Layout>
